      "content": "The only way to truly \"protect\" users is to empower them to make their own decisions, rather than relying on government-mandated moderation. Any regulation that seeks to shield users from certain viewpoints is, by definition, a form of censorship. The only way to ensure \"safe\" regulation is to have a robust system of user-led moderation, where individuals can freely express themselves without fear of government reprisal. This approach would require a fundamental shift in the way we think about free speech, from a government-provided safety net to a user-driven, decentralized model.",
